The Core Problem: Unmitigated [X.X]x Leverage Breaches [X.X]x Policy
 * A simplistic, all-debt financing approach results in ~[X.X]x peak leverage.
 * This leverage level would likely trigger immediate rating agency action to ‘BBB’, imposing a permanent and significant funding cost penalty.
Proposed Architecture: A Phased, De-risked Path to <[X.X]x Leverage
 * Day 1: Underwritten Bridge + ABB to achieve ~[X.X]x leverage, immediately signaling credit discipline.
 * Take-Out: Investment Grade Bonds + Securitization to lock in permanent capital and reach ~[X.X]x leverage.
 * Steady State: Free Cash Flow + Synergies drive leverage to the long-term target of <[X.X]x.
