Chart Description: Synergy Waterfall
 * Chart Type: A standard waterfall chart visually bridging from a starting value to an ending value.
 * Y-Axis: Monetary value in millions of Euros (€m).
 * X-Axis: Categorical, representing the components of the EBITDA build-up.
 * Data Series: The chart will begin with a bar representing Schenker's Standalone LTM EBITDA. It will be followed by a series of positive (green) bars, each representing a key synergy category (e.g., "Margin Uplift," "Network Optimisation," "IT Consolidation," "Overhead Removal"). The chart will conclude with a final bar representing the total Pro-Forma Synergized EBITDA. The value for each bar is derived from the synergy quantification model.
 * Purpose: To clearly and intuitively illustrate how the identified synergies build upon the target's standalone profitability to arrive at the final, enhanced earnings profile that underpins the deal's value.
Slide 3: Credit Impact Analysis: ‘A-’ vs. ‘BBB’ Scenarios
Layout Guidance: A pure credit analysis sheet. It uses a technical description of a credit curve chart to visually prove the quantifiable cost of a credit rating downgrade.
Content & Visuals:
The “Fallen Angel” Penalty is Quantifiable and Permanent
 * Our proposed architecture is explicitly designed to avoid key rating agency downgrade triggers, which we expect would include sustained leverage approaching [X.X]x (Moody’s-adjusted) or FFO/Debt remaining below [XX]% (S&P standard).
 * On a €[X]bn bond take-out, a ~[XXX] bps spread differential between ‘A-’ and ‘BBB’ ratings results in:
   * ~€[XXX]m in additional annual interest expense.
   * ~€[XXX]m in Net Present Value destruction.
Underlying Justifications & Assumptions
 * NPV Calculation: The NPV destruction figure is calculated based on the present value of the ~€[XXX]m annual penalty, using an assumed [X.X]% DSV Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC) over a [Y]-year period, aligning with the likely average tenor of the new bond issuance.
Chart Description: Credit Spread Curve Analysis
 * Chart Type: A scatter plot with two distinct best-fit trend lines (curves).
 * Y-Axis: Credit Spread over the risk-free benchmark, measured in basis points (bps).
 * X-Axis: Tenor/Maturity, measured in years (e.g., from 1Y to 10Y).
 * Data Series: The plot will feature two sets of data points. Each point represents an outstanding bond from a peer company (e.g., Deutsche Post, UPS), sourced from market data. The points will be categorised by their credit rating. A curve will be fitted through the 'A' rated peers, and a separate, higher curve will be fitted through the 'BBB' rated peers.
 * Purpose & Annotation: To visually demonstrate the material and non-linear increase in funding costs between the two rating categories. The chart will be annotated at the key [Y-Z] year tenor (where new issuance is likely) to explicitly highlight the ~[XXX] bps spread differential, making the cost of a downgrade tangible.
Slide 4: Phased Deleveraging & Ratings Path
Layout Guidance: Dominated by a verbal description of a single, clear “Leverage Walk” chart, a standard visualization in leveraged finance pitches.
Content & Visuals:
Why <[X.X]x is Critical: The Policy / Capacity Distinction
 * While DSV’s balance sheet could mechanically support higher leverage, strict adherence to the <[X.X]x Net Debt/EBITDA policy is critical for a strategic reason: it preserves financial and strategic flexibility.
 * Maintaining this discipline ensures continued access to the commercial paper market at favorable rates and, most importantly, retains balance sheet capacity to pursue the next strategic acquisition without needing a multi-year deleveraging period first.
Chart Description: Pro-Forma Leverage Walk
 * Chart Type: A standard waterfall chart, illustrating a step-by-step reduction from a starting point.
 * Y-Axis: Net Debt / EBITDA leverage multiple, expressed as [X.X]x.
 * X-Axis: Categorical, representing the sequence of the transaction and deleveraging events.
 * Data Series: The chart begins with a tall bar showing the high Unmitigated Pro-Forma Leverage. Each subsequent bar is negative (red), representing a reduction in leverage from a specific action: "ABB Equity Injection (-[X.X]x)," "Securitization & FCF (-[X.X]x)," and "Future Synergies & FCF (-[X.X]x)." The chart ends on the final, lower Steady-State Leverage. A horizontal dotted line will be drawn across the chart at the [X.X]x Policy Ceiling.
 * Purpose & Annotation: To provide a clear, mechanical illustration of how our proposed financing architecture navigates the leverage challenge. The key message is that the company's leverage is immediately brought below the policy ceiling after Day 1 actions, satisfying rating agencies and demonstrating financial discipline.
