 * Pricing Rationale: New issue will be priced relative to secondary market levels of key comps, primarily Deutsche Post (A-), with a standard new issue concession.
Chart Description: Peer Secondary Curve Analysis
 * Chart Type: A scatter plot with individual data points for peer bonds and a single indicative point for the proposed new issue.
 * Y-Axis: Credit Spread over the benchmark, measured in basis points (bps).
 * X-Axis: Tenor/Maturity, measured in years.
 * Data Series: The plot will show discrete points, each representing a key secondary bond from close peers (e.g., "Peer Co. 1 'BBB'," "Peer Co. 2 'A-'," "Peer Co. 3 'A'"). A separate, distinct point, labelled "DSV Indicative New Issue," will be placed at the target tenor (e.g., [B]Y) and at a spread slightly above the closest 'A-' peer to reflect a standard new issue premium.
 * Purpose & Annotation: To provide a clear market-based rationale for our pricing assumptions. It demonstrates to the client how their new debt would be priced relative to their closest publicly-traded competitors, justifying the target spread of ~[XXX] bps.
2. SFS: The €[X.X]bn “Smart” Deleveraging
 * Instrument: Off-balance sheet securitization of a select pool of high-quality German trade receivables.
 * Asset Quality & Structural Assumptions:
   * The structure is modeled on an assumed pool with a historical net loss rate of <[X.XX]%, average days sales outstanding (DSO) of ~[XX] days, and a highly granular obligor base.
   * Assumes a standard advance rate of [XX]% against the eligible receivables pool.
 * Economic Benefit: Provides funding at an estimated EURIBOR + ~[XX]bps, representing a ~[XXX] bps saving vs. unsecured bond debt.
